<subSubSection id="C33C655DFFA0FFCEFDFFF9E9FD01F8E0" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9936D6FFA0FFCEFDFFF9E9FD01F8E0" blockId="4.[151,1436,1627,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B27FFA0FFCEFDFFF9E9FCBCF9DE" author="Ineich, I. &amp; Rasmussen, A. R." box="[544,883,1628,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref12781" refString="Ineich, I. &amp; Rasmussen, A. R. (1997) Sea snakes from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands (Elapidae, Laticaudinae and Hydrophiinae). Zoosystema, 19, 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1997">Ineich and Rasmussen (1997)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D55FFA0FFCEFC22F9E8FBB9F9DE" baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[1021,1142,1628,1653]" class="Reptilia" family="Elapidae" genus="Hydrophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spiralis">
<emphasis id="B952EAC4FFA0FFCEFC22F9E8FBB9F9DE" box="[1021,1142,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. spiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time in 
<collectingCountry id="F3317646FFA0FFCEFAB8F9E9FEC3F933" name="New Caledonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, which is surprising, as it has never been collected in 
<collectingCounty id="62F84E5AFFA0FFCEFCAFF9CAFC2AF933" box="[880,997,1663,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Australian</collectingCounty>
waters. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BFDACACFFA0FFCEFB9AF9CAFBBEF933" box="[1093,1137,1663,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">The</collectingMunicipality>
known distributions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D55FFA0FFCEFA5EF934FF24F916" baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1802" class="Reptilia" family="Elapidae" genus="Hydrophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spiralis">
<emphasis id="B952EAC4FFA0FFCEFA5EF934FF24F916" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. spiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the 
<location id="8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFE9AF911FE1CF916" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:038F87C0FFA0FFCEFF48F9EEFD01F8E0:8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFE9AF911FE1CF916" box="[325,467,1700,1725]" country="New Caledonia" county="Australian" municipality="The" name="Persian Gulf" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" stateProvince="Java and Sulawesi">Persian Gulf</location>
in the west to 
<collectingCountry id="F3317646FFA0FFCEFDA7F911FD18F916" box="[632,727,1700,1725]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
in the east, 
<collectingCountry id="F3317646FFA0FFCEFC81F911FC04F916" box="[862,971,1700,1725]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
including 
<collectingRegion id="49E2F834FFA0FFCEFB9BF911FADEF916" box="[1092,1297,1700,1725]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Java and Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
in the south (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B27FFA0FFCEFF41F972FE5AF94B" author="David, P. &amp; Ineich, I." box="[158,405,1735,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" pagination="3 - 499" refId="ref12041" refString="David, P. &amp; Ineich, I. (1999) Les serpents venimeux du monde: systematique et repartition. Dumerilia (Paris), 3, 3 - 499." type="journal article" year="1999">David &amp; Ineich, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; Rasmussen, Elmberg, 
<emphasis id="B952EAC4FFA0FFCEFD46F97CFD1EF94B" box="[665,721,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011). 
<location id="8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFCF4F972FC44F94B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:038F87C0FFA0FFCEFF48F9EEFD01F8E0:8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFCF4F972FC44F94B" box="[811,907,1735,1760]" country="New Caledonia" county="Australian" municipality="The" name="Whether" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" stateProvince="Java and Sulawesi">Whether</location>
it was a vagrant specimen from 
<location id="8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFB2BF972FAE7F94B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:038F87C0FFA0FFCEFF48F9EEFD01F8E0:8EF9600DFFA0FFCEFB2BF972FAE7F94B" box="[1268,1320,1735,1760]" country="New Caledonia" county="Australian" municipality="The" name="Asia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" stateProvince="Java and Sulawesi">Asia</location>
or there is a population at 
<collectingCountry id="F3317646FFA0FFCEFE94F959FE34F8AE" box="[331,507,1772,1797]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
is uncertain, but with only 
<specimenCount id="9D20FD5FFFA0FFCEFCE4F959FC18F8AE" box="[827,983,1772,1797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
collected from 
<collectingCountry id="F3317646FFA0FFCEFB51F959FAF1F8AE" box="[1166,1342,1772,1797]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
without precise locality (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B27FFA0FFCEFE8EF8BAFD48F883" author="Ineich, I. &amp; Rasmussen, A. R." box="[337,647,1807,1832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref12781" refString="Ineich, I. &amp; Rasmussen, A. R. (1997) Sea snakes from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands (Elapidae, Laticaudinae and Hydrophiinae). Zoosystema, 19, 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1997">Ineich &amp; Rasmussen, 1997</bibRefCitation>
), we do not include it in the possible list until further specimens have confirmed its presence closer to Australian waters.
</paragraph>
